<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="bare-adj">bare <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /beə(r)/    美 /ber/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>赤裸的；光秃秃的；空的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>bare feet</strong> 
光脚</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a bare hill / shelf 
光秃秃的山/空无一物的架子</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The man in the photo was bare to the waist. 
照片上的男子赤裸着上身。</p><footer>外研⑦ – 5</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>仅有的；最低限度的</strong></h4>
<p>just enough; the most basic or simple：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the <strong>bare minimum</strong> of furniture 
最基本的家具</p></div></div>